theorem Topology.P2_compl_iff_P3_compl_of_isOpen
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (hA : IsOpen A) :
    Topology.P2 (Aᶜ) ↔ Topology.P3 (Aᶜ) := by
  -- The complement of an open set is closed.
  have hClosed : IsClosed (Aᶜ) := (isOpen_compl_iff).1 hA
  -- Apply the equivalence for closed sets.
  simpa using (Topology.P2_iff_P3_of_isClosed (A := Aᶜ) hClosed)

theorem Topology.isClosed_compl_of_isOpen
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (hA : IsOpen A) :
    IsClosed (Aᶜ) := by
  -- View `A` as the double complement of itself so that we can
  -- directly apply `isOpen_compl_iff`.
  have hOpenDoubleCompl : IsOpen ((Aᶜ)ᶜ) := by
    simpa [Set.compl_compl] using hA
  -- Now obtain the desired closedness from the equivalence.
  simpa using (isOpen_compl_iff.mp hOpenDoubleCompl)

theorem Set.compl_compl {α : Type*} (s : Set α) : sᶜᶜ = s := by
  ext x
  simp
